title: BUILD_INSIGHTS=1 python setup.py develop FAILURE
body:
Failed during installation.

I run the code 
`BUILD_INSIGHTS=1 python setup.py develop
`
> - Building version 0.4.0
> -- Building Captum Insights
> Running: ./scripts/build_insights.sh
> ~/junyan/Python/explainable_ai/captum/captum/insights/attr_vis/frontend ~/junyan/Python/explainable_ai/captum
> -----------------------------------
> Install Dependencies
> -----------------------------------
> yarn install v1.22.10
> [1/4] Resolving packages...
> success Already up-to-date.
> Done in 0.58s.
> -----------------------------------
> Building Captum Insights
> -----------------------------------
> yarn run v1.22.10
> $ react-scripts build --ignore-engines
> /home/ubuntu/junyan/Python/explainable_ai/captum/captum/insights/attr_vis/frontend/node_modules/react-scripts/config/webpack.config.js:306
>         ...(isEnvProductionProfile && {
>         ^^^
> 
> SyntaxError: Unexpected token ...
>     at createScript (vm.js:56:10)
>     at Object.runInThisContext (vm.js:97:10)
>     at Module._compile (module.js:549:28)
>     at Object.Module._extensions..js (module.js:586:10)
>     at Module.load (module.js:494:32)
>     at tryModuleLoad (module.js:453:12)
>     at Function.Module._load (module.js:445:3)
>     at Module.require (module.js:504:17)
>     at require (internal/module.js:20:19)
>     at Object.<anonymous> (/home/ubuntu/junyan/Python/explainable_ai/captum/captum/insights/attr_vis/frontend/node_modules/react-scripts/scripts/build.js:38:23)
> error Command failed with exit code 1.
> info Visit https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs/cli/run for documentation about this command.
> Traceback (most recent call last):
>   File "setup.py", line 112, in <module>
>     build_insights()
>   File "setup.py", line 95, in build_insights
>     subprocess.check_call(command)
>   File "/home/ubuntu/anaconda3/lib/python3.8/subprocess.py", line 364, in check_call
>     raise CalledProcessError(retcode, cmd)
> subprocess.CalledProcessError: Command './scripts/build_insights.sh' returned non-zero exit status 1.

I do not know what cause the problem.

I use "yarn install --ignore-engines" instead of "yarn install" in the script.

Same problem for both two statements.

Therefore, what is the root cause for the problem and how can I resolve it?

Regards!
Momo
